playd is a simple mplayer wrapper written in pure /bin/sh

playd controls mplayer daemon via pipe.

FEATURES:
* written in sh
* very lightwidth
* cli interface
* supports playlists
* supports all file types supported by mplayer
* supports streaming
* supports jumping to next, previous or any other playlist item
* playlist randomization (alternative to shuffle in ordinary audio players)
* very fast
* create/load playlists, create special playlist with favourite songs
* display status
* easy to learn and use

REQUIREMENTS:
* mplayer
* /bin/sh
* standard Unix tools sed, akw, grep, find
* jot (some linux doesn't have it instaled by default)
* procstat or lsof
* tagutil (optional, needef if you want playd info to work)

